This paper focuses on attacking generative models such as VAE and GAN, which are commonly used in computer vision and machine learning applications. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of deep neural networks, which falls under the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper also discusses the vulnerability of generative models to adversarial attacks, which falls under the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
